channel.title: !errors!
channel.description:
Ok I am using Allstar's client and I recently saw that on all his methods and custom commands of "Thieving"' he spelt [b]Theif[/b] and it is really spelled with an [b]ie[/b] when I replaced all instance of his incorrect spelling with the ctrl+h command I went a compiled and this is what I came up with.
[code]13 errors
method cannot find symbol[/code]
It said that for each of the 13 errors. All help is appreciated.

item.title: !errors!
item.dc:creator: @dogzound5 dogzound5@gmail.com
item.description:
@dogzound5 wrote:

I fixed the problem. It came from one thieving stall this is what the code was.

case 635: thiefStall(".", ".", 1, 5 * playerLevel[17], 995, 250, 30, 0x340); break;

I guess in game that did not match up with the right method so it didnt compile.

I just found the object ID and changed it

case 635: thiefStall("Tea stall", "and recieve 250gp", 1, 5 * playerLevel[17], 995, 250, 30, 0x340); break;

All is good now.

Read full topic
